      "comment": "SILENT THINKER (9) looked handy placing at the Gold Coast on debut and will have derived a stack of benefit from that race day experience. Gets the services of in-form hoop Thompson in the irons and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. ZOUS A CHANCE (10) was at cricket score odds when facing the starter for the first time but defied expectations with a solid third beaten only two lengths. Jockey Taylor stays on top and looks a genuine top-three candidate with natural improvement. SAVASTEEL (2) has placed three of five overall and maps nicely for this from gate two. In the mix. CAUTIONARY TAIL (3) next best in a race with only a handful of chances.",
